I"×<h3 id="broccoli-salad">Broccoli Salad</h3>
<ul>
  <li>1 head of Broccoli (5 cups of florets)</li>
  <li>8 slices of bacon</li>
  <li>1/3 cup of red onion</li>
  <li>1/2 cup dried cranberries</li>
  <li>1/2 cup sunflower seeds</li>
  <li>1/4 goat cheese, crumbled</li>
  <li>Dressing:</li>
  <li>1/2 cup mayo</li>
  <li>1/4 cup yogurt</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="procedure">Procedure:</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Bake or fry the bacon per package instructions. Pat excess grease.</li>
  <li>Chop broccoli into bite size florets. Add to large mixing bowl with cranberries, sunflower seeds and goat cheese.</li>
  <li>Dressing: mix mayo and yogurt in small bowl. Then add dressing to large mixing bowl and stir until everything is mixed.</li>
</ol>
